    "rawBody": "- **Source / inspiration URL:** https://braziliankitchenabroad.com/picanha-brazilian-culotte-steaks/ ⚠ REFERENCE (non-vegan / technique) *(Brazilian Kitchen Abroad's recipe is for real-beef culotte steaks — the technique reference for the salt-cure, fat-cap-up sear, and tableside slicing. **Recommended: Juicy Marbles Whole-Cut Loin** (or stacked Thick-Cut Filets). Salt absorption, sear behavior, and rest times all differ vs. real picanha — JM's loin renders fat differently, calibrate during a service test.)*\n- **Description:** **Lead protein:** Juicy Marbles Whole-Cut Loin (or stacked Thick-Cut Filets). Heavily salted with rock salt, skewered fat-cap-up (the loin's marbling reads as fat cap), seared/flame-roasted on a churrasqueira rotisserie or ripping-hot plancha, rested, then sliced thin against the grain tableside or à la minute. Served with chimichurri or salsa vinagrete + farofa. The Brazilian centerpiece, plant-based.\n- **Wholesale food cost:** $11.80 / serving (1 × JM Loin portion ≈ 6 oz @ ~$32/lb wholesale + sides) · **Menu price:** **$32–38** (steakhouse tier ÷ 0.30)\n- **Weight:** 360 g (steak + farofa + vinagrete) · **Calories:** 580 · **Protein:** 36 g · **Time:** 35 min (incl. 30-min salt rest) · **Servings:** 1\n- **Restaurant difficulty:** **Hard** — open flame or plancha + 30-min salt cure + rest + slice + plated sides; this is your signature dish, plate one at a time.\n- **Tags:** (neither — purely cooked-to-order)\n\n| Sub | Effect | Cost delta |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Lead protein:** Juicy Marbles Whole-Cut Loin (default) | Largest plant-meat cut; best presentation | baseline |\n| Juicy Marbles Thick-Cut Filet × 2 stacked | Easier portion control | −$2.20 |\n| Chunk Foods Steakhouse Cut 6 oz | More savings, slightly less marbling drama | −$5.80 |\n| Beyond Steak Tips on skewer (espetinho) | Casual-tier picanha-espetinho variant | −$7.50 (menu repositions to $19–22) |",
