    "id": "brazilian-vegan-brigadeiro",
    "title": "Brigadeiro (Sem crueldade)",
    "source": "Pies and Tacos",
    "rawTitle": "### Vegan Brigadeiro (**DESSERT**)",
    "rawBody": "- **URL:** https://www.piesandtacos.com/vegan-brigadeiros-vegan-truffles/ ✓ VERIFIED *(Pies and Tacos by Camila Hurst — a Brazilian baker, so this is an authoritative source. Note: Camila's recipe is a paleo / refined-sugar-free variant that uses **maple syrup + coconut butter + nut butter + vegan chocolate chips** rather than the traditional Brazilian approach with sweetened condensed milk. This is a meaningful flavor and ingredient deviation from \"classic\" brigadeiro — the texture is more of a dense fudge truffle than the chewy soft-roll of the original — but the result is genuinely vegan, gluten-free, and refined-sugar-free, which positions well for an upscale Brazilian menu.)*\n\n  **Recipe** (10 pieces / batch, per Camila Hurst): 1/4 cup maple syrup, 1/4 cup coconut butter (NOT coconut oil — she's specific), 2 tbsp cashew butter (or other neutral nut butter), 1/4 cup vegan chocolate chips. Combine all ingredients in a small saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly. Heat until everything is melted and the mixture is smooth — *do not let it come to a full boil*. Pour into a heatproof bowl, cool to room temperature, then chill in the fridge 10–20 minutes until rollable consistency (not too stiff, not too soft — texture varies with kitchen temp). Scoop teaspoon-sized portions, roll into balls, coat in dairy-free sprinkles / chopped nuts / cacao nibs / shredded coconut. Refrigerated, holds up to 8 days; freezes up to 1 month.\n\n- **Description:** Paleo-style chocolate fudge truffles built on maple syrup, coconut butter, cashew butter, and vegan chocolate chips, rolled and coated in dairy-free sprinkles. The classic Brazilian birthday-party sweet, reimagined refined-sugar-free and gluten-free. Plates as a 3- or 5-piece bite-sized dessert; the *de rigueur* finish at any Brazilian restaurant.\n- **Wholesale food cost:** $0.45 / piece (~$1.35 / 3-piece — slightly higher than the traditional condensed-coconut-milk version because coconut butter and cashew butter are pricier than condensed milk, but partially offset by the small batch size) · **Menu price:** **$5–7** (3-piece) / **$7–9** (5-piece) / **$9–12** (mixed brigadeiro flight: chocolate + branco + churros-cinnamon)\n- **Weight:** 25 g / piece · **Calories:** 110 · **Protein:** 1 g · **Time:** 5 min cook + 15–30 min cool + 10 min roll · **Servings:** 10 pieces / batch\n- **Restaurant difficulty:** **Easy** — bulk-batch, roll & coat during prep, refrigerate up to 8 days, plate cold.\n- **Tags:** 🥘 Bulk-Prep · ⚡ Fast-Service\n\n| Sub | Effect | Cost delta |\n|---|---|---|\n| Pies and Tacos paleo brigadeiro (Camila Hurst, default) | Paleo / GF / refined-sugar-free; verified vegan | baseline ($0.45) |\n| Traditional vegan brigadeiro: sweetened condensed coconut milk (Nature's Charm) + cocoa + vegan butter | Closer to authentic Brazilian texture (chewy, sticky); cheaper at scale | −$0.10 → $0.35 / pc |\n| Brigadeiro branco (white coconut, no chocolate) | Pair-tier alongside chocolate | flat |\n| Beijinho (white coconut + clove + sprinkles) | Cousin sweet | flat |\n| Mixed-brigadeiro flight of 3 flavors | Premium menu listing | +$1.20 → menu $9–12 |",
